&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Surveillance and Response HCA – Band 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you motivated, flexible and looking for a new challenge?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the fast paced and ever developing COVID swabbing testing team as a Surveillance and Response HCA.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will cover MPH the Community with regular travel across all sites. For this reason applicants must be able to drive and hold car insurance which covers business use.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working hours are between 08:30 and 16:30 (approximately) Monday to Sunday, on a rota basis, at the present time however this may be subject to change due to service demand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time 37.5 hours per week, part time considered .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note this vacancy may close early if enough applicants have applied&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
